s of his novels show the profoundly collaborative nature of these works.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish dramay20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aA Kestrel for a Knave.  aBarry Hines.  aConservative government.  aKen Loach.  aLooks and Smiles.  aSouth Yorkshire.  aThreads.  aaesthetic production.  aclass issues.  aliterary reception.  aminers' strike.  aplace issues.  apoetic realism.  aspace issues.  aworking-class film.  aworking-class television.  aworking-class writing.1 aForrest, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVice, Sue, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVice, Sue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612374940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526123749423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526123749/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles